            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> cold coastlines<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or colony (3\u201320)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "These short-winged and short-tailed birds favor cold rocky islands. They dine primarily on fish. Their beak retains its color through the mating season, and then the color is shed off, revealing a smaller, muted beak.<br/><br/> Puffins are about a foot long and weigh close to 1 pound."
        }
    ],
